# Testing Strategy & Implementation Guide

This project uses a multi-layered testing approach aligned with the testing pyramid: unit tests for fast feedback, integration tests for component interactions, and E2E tests for user workflows.

## Testing Architecture

### Testing Pyramid

```
Unit Tests (Vitest + RTL)
  ↑ Many, fast, isolated

Integration Tests (Vitest + RTL)
  ↑ Component interactions

E2E Tests (Playwright)
  ↑ Few, high-level user flows
```

## Tools & Frameworks

### Unit & Integration Testing

- **Vitest** - Fast unit test framework
- **@testing-library/react** - React component testing utilities

### End-to-End Testing

- **Playwright** - E2E testing framework

## Test Organization

### Hybrid Structure

Tests are organized using a hybrid approach combining co-location with dedicated test directories:

```
apps/admin/src/
├── entities/
│   └── destination/
│       ├── __tests__/              ← Dedicated test folder
│       │   ├── destination-utils.test.ts
│       │   └── useDestinations.test.tsx
│       ├── api/
│       ├── lib/
│       └── model/
├── features/
│   └── destination-search/
│       ├── __tests__/              ← Dedicated test folder
│       │   ├── DestinationSearchInput.test.tsx
│       │   └── useDestinationSearch.test.tsx
│       ├── model/
│       └── ui/
└── widgets/
    └── destination-tree/
        ├── __tests__/              ← Dedicated test folder
        │   └── DestinationTree.test.tsx
        ├── model/
        └── ui/

apps/admin/e2e/
└── tests/                          ← E2E tests separate
    ├── destination-search.spec.ts
    └── destination-tree.spec.ts
```

**Key Pattern**: Use `__tests__/` folder at the feature/widget/entity root level for consistency.

## Running Tests

### Unit/Integration Tests

```bash
# Run all tests
pnpm test

# Run in watch mode
pnpm test:watch

# Run with coverage
pnpm test:coverage

# Run specific test file
pnpm test destination-utils.test.ts
```

### E2E Tests

```bash
# Run all E2E tests
pnpm test:e2e

# Run in UI mode
pnpm test:e2e:ui

# Run specific test file
pnpm test:e2e destination-tree.spec.ts

# Run in debug mode
pnpm test:e2e:debug
```

## Best Practices Summary

### Do's ✅

- ✅ Test behavior, not implementation
- ✅ Use semantic queries (`getByRole`, `getByText`)
- ✅ Group related tests with `describe` blocks
- ✅ Use descriptive test names
- ✅ Mock external dependencies
- ✅ Test edge cases and error scenarios
- ✅ Wait for state changes in E2E tests
- ✅ Use test data factories for consistency
- ✅ Keep tests isolated and independent
- ✅ Follow AAA pattern (Arrange, Act, Assert)
- ✅ Place test files in `__tests__/` folder at feature/widget/entity root

### Don'ts ❌

- ❌ Don't use `waitForTimeout` in E2E tests
- ❌ Don't test implementation details
- ❌ Don't rely on test execution order
- ❌ Don't skip cleanup (`afterEach`, `afterAll`)
- ❌ Don't use non-semantic selectors (`data-testid` unless necessary)
- ❌ Don't test third-party library code
- ❌ Don't write tests that depend on other tests
- ❌ Don't ignore flaky tests — fix them
- ❌ Don't scatter test files across subdirectories — use `__tests__/` at root level

## Test File Naming

- Unit/Integration tests: `*.test.ts` or `*.test.tsx`
- E2E tests: `*.spec.ts`
- Test files should be co-located in `__tests__/` folders

